{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":89309,"duration_api_ms":89259,"num_turns":10,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"7016238f-248a-4aef-8b98-8fbb46b4f47b","total_cost_usd":0.41792855000000007,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":29839,"cache_read_input_tokens":226857,"output_tokens":2434,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":29839,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":8,"outputTokens":2434,"cacheReadInputTokens":226857,"cacheCreationInputTokens":29839,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.36081225,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":30,"outputTokens":3955,"cacheReadInputTokens":77463,"cacheCreationInputTokens":23652,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.05711630000000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All three amendments identify genuine bugs in the plan_hash auto-population and runless fallback matching logic. Amendments fr-1-0b213bd9 and fr-1-929f7a9f describe the same root cause (unconditional plan_hash auto-population at the service boundary breaks idempotent replay after plan evolution) from complementary angles, and both should be accepted since they propose different (compatible) fix strategies. Amendment fr-1-b656ac14 identifies a real missing started_at guard in the runless fallback path that could cause wrong-attempt finalization.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-1-0b213bd9","decision":"accept","rationale":"The scenario is valid and reproducible: (1) bead completes with plan_hash=None, auto-populated to hash_v1 and stored; (2) persist_plan updates snapshot.plan_hash to hash_v2; (3) idempotent replay of the same completion with plan_hash=None now auto-populates to hash_v2; (4) option_conflicts(Some(hash_v1), Some(hash_v2)) at fs.rs:3161 returns true, triggering a spurious incompatible_terminal_update error. Pre-change behavior (passing None through) was correct because option_conflicts(Some(x), None) is always false, allowing harmless replays. The proposed fixes — either skip auto-population when the entry is already terminal, or weaken the terminal replay conflict check to treat plan_hash mismatch as non-fatal when the stored entry already has a plan_hash (backfill-only semantics) — are both sound approaches. This is a real idempotency violation that would break crash-recovery replay."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-b656ac14","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed by reading the code: at fs.rs:3018, the runless fallback path accepts `[index] if entries[*index].run_id.is_none()` without any started_at validation. Compare with the non-run_id path (line 3077-3081) which explicitly filters by `entries[*index].started_at == started_at`. The service contract at service.rs:464-469 explicitly documents that started_at is forwarded to the lineage layer for deterministic replay of runless completions. Without the started_at check, a completion targeting attempt A (started at time T1) could finalize attempt B (started at time T2) if B happens to be the only open runless entry with the right bead/project. This violates the contract and could corrupt lineage data. Adding `entries[*index].started_at == started_at` as a guard is straightforward and correct."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-929f7a9f","decision":"accept","rationale":"This amendment correctly identifies the same root cause as fr-1-0b213bd9 but focuses on the service-layer fix: the auto-population at service.rs:429-433 and 564-568 is unconditional (`plan_hash.or_else(|| snapshot.plan_hash.clone())`), meaning it replaces None with the *current* snapshot plan_hash before the adapter's matching logic runs. After persist_plan advances snapshot.plan_hash, replays of starts/completions for rows recorded under the old plan will now carry the new hash, tripping the conflict checks at fs.rs:2711-2725 (for starts) and fs.rs:3159-3201 (for completions). The proposed fix — only auto-populate when the matched row lacks plan_hash, not blindly at the service boundary — correctly scopes the backfill to its intended purpose. The request for replay-across-plan-update test coverage is also well-justified since this is a subtle interaction between two features (auto-population and plan evolution) that has no coverage today."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"8226cdf0-5036-486b-be5d-17f88d8edec6"}
